docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, Feb. 24 (AP).-- The Rev. Philip Lindsay, who believes he was one of the last persons to sight the Danish training frigate Kobenhavn, missing with all hands since last Winter, thinks the ship went to the bottom near the rocky shoals off the lonely South Atlantic island of Tristan da Cunha.
